{"title_page": "Bibliography of Pope Pius XII", "text_new": "{{short description|Wikipedia bibliography}}\n{{main|Pope Pius XII}}\nThis '''bibliography on Church policies 1939&ndash;1945'''{{clarify|date=May 2019}} includes mainly [[Italy|Italian]] publications relative to [[Pope Pius XII]] and [[Holy See|Vatican]] policies during [[World War II]] . Two areas are missing and need separate bibliographies at a later date.\n\n* The bibliography does not include theology, theological issues and publications on the [[Theology of Pope Pius XII]], [[Mariology of Pope Pius XII]], on his ecclesiastical promulgations such as the [[Dogma (Roman Catholic)|dogma]] of the [[Assumption of Mary|Assumption]] of the [[Blessed Virgin Mary (Roman Catholic)|Virgin Mary]], [[Pope Pius XII Liturgy Reforms|Church reforms]], or, the [[Beatifications of Pope Pius XII]] [[Saints canonized by Pope Pius XII]], [[List of encyclicals of Pope Pius XII|Encyclicals of the Pontiff]] and other theological issues.\n* Policies after World War Two are also not included such as [[Pope Pius XII Church policies after World War II]], [[Persecutions of the Catholic Church and Pius XII]], and Vatican policies regarding the Church in [[Pope Pius XII and Russia|Russia]], [[Pope Pius XII and Poland|Poland]] and [[Pope Pius XII and the Church in China|China]] and other countries.\n\n== A ==\n* ADSS &ndash; ''[[Actes et documents du Saint Si\u00e8ge relatifs \u00e0 la Seconde Guerre Mondiale|Actes et Documents du Saint-Si\u00e8ge relatifs \u00e0 la Seconde guerre mondiale]]''. Libreria Editrice Vaticana, Citt\u00e0 del Vaticano 1972. {{in lang|en|fr|it}}\n* [[Giorgio Angelozzi Gariboldi]]. ''Pio XII, Hitler e Mussolini''. Mursia, Milano 1988. {{ISBN|88-425-2875-7}}\n* [[Mark Aarons]] e [[John Loftus (author)|John Loftus]]. ''Unholy Trinity: The Vatican, The Nazist and the Swiss Banks''. St Martin\u2019s Press, [[New York City|New York]] 1998. {{ISBN|0-312-18199-X}}. {{in lang|en}}\n* [[David Alvaretz]]. ''Spie in V